[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now as Jesus was passing by,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he saw a man who had been blind from birth. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " His disciples asked him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Rabbi, who committed the sin that caused him to be born blind, this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " or his parents?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus answered, “Neither this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " nor his parents sinned, but he was born blind so that"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the acts"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of God may be revealed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " through what happens to him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We must perform the deeds"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the one who sent me"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as long as"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it is daytime. Night is coming when no one can work. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Having said this,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he spat on the ground and made some mud"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " with the saliva. He"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " smeared the mud on the blind man’s"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " eyes "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said to him, “Go wash in the pool of Siloam”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (which is translated “sent”)."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the blind man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went away and washed, and came back seeing."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the neighbors and the people who had seen him previously"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as a beggar began saying,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Is this not the man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who used to sit and beg?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Some people said,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “This is the man!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " while others said, “No, but he looks like him.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The man himself"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " kept insisting, “I am the one!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So they asked him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “How then were you made to see?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “The man called Jesus made mud,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " smeared it"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on my eyes and told me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘Go to Siloam and wash.’ So I went and washed, and was able to see.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They said"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to him, “Where is that man?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I don’t know.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They brought the man who used to be blind"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the Pharisees."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now the day on which Jesus made the mud"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and caused him to see"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was a Sabbath.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So the Pharisees asked him again how he had gained his sight."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “He put mud"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on my eyes and I washed, and now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I am able to see.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then some of the Pharisees began to say,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “This man is not from God, because he does not observe"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the Sabbath.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But others said, “How can a man who is a sinner perform"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " such miraculous signs?” Thus there was a division"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " among them. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So again they asked the man who used to be blind,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “What do you say about him, since he caused you to see?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “He is a prophet,” the man replied."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now the Jewish religious leaders"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " refused to believe"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that he had really been blind and had gained his sight until at last they summoned"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the parents of the man who had become able to see."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They asked the parents,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Is this your son, whom you say"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " was born blind? Then how does he now see?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So his parents replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We know that this is our son and that he was born blind. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But we do not know how he is now able to see, nor do we know who caused him to see."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Ask him, he is a mature adult."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He will speak for himself.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (His parents said these things because they were afraid of the Jewish religious leaders."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the Jewish leaders had already agreed that anyone who confessed Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to be the Christ"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " would be put out"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the synagogue."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For this reason his parents said, “He is a mature adult,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ask him.”)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then they summoned"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the man who used to be blind"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a second time and said to him, “Promise before God to tell the truth."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We know that this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is a sinner.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I do not know whether he is a sinner. I do know one thing – that although I was blind, now I can see.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then they said to him, “What did he do to you? How did he cause you to see?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He answered,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I told you already and you didn’t listen."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Why do you want to hear it"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " again? You people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " don’t want to become his disciples too, do you?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " heaped insults"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on him, saying,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “You are his disciple!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We are disciples of Moses! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We know that God has spoken to Moses! We do not know where this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " comes from!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The man replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “This is a remarkable thing,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that you don’t know where he comes from, and yet he caused me to see!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We know that God doesn’t listen to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sinners, but if anyone is devout"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and does his will, God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " listens to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Never before"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has anyone heard of someone causing a man born blind to see."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " If this man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " were not from God, he could do nothing.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “You were born completely in sinfulness,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and yet you presume to teach us?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So they threw him out."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus heard that they had thrown him out, so he found the man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said to him, “Do you believe in the Son of Man?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The man"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “And who is he, sir, that"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I may believe in him?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus told him, “You have seen him; he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is the one speaking with you.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " [ "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said, “Lord, I believe,” and he worshiped him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said,]"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “For judgment I have come into this world, so that those who do not see may gain their sight,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the ones who see may become blind.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Some of the Pharisees"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who were with him heard this"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and asked him,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We are not blind too, are we?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Jesus replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “If you were blind, you would not be guilty of sin,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but now because you claim that you can see,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your guilt"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " remains.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]